@piiswrong @tqchen Suppose you have a function "Predict", and its maximum GPU memory consumption is 1GB. After you call Predict(), the occupied GPU memory will not be released. If you call Predict() again, then memory occupied will be 2GB. After you program terminates, all the memory will be released finally.

